`std::vector<long long> solve(std::vector<std::vector<long long>> matrix)`

Let $N$ be the size of the matrix.
1. Initialize a result vector `ans` of size $N$ with zeros.
2. Loop $i$ from 0 to $N-1$. (Iterating over vertices)
3. Initialize `degree` for vertex $i$ to 0.
4. Loop $j$ from 0 to $N-1$. (Iterating over neighbors)
5. If `matrix[i][j] == 1`, increment `degree`.
6. Set `ans[i] = degree`.
